	number = {1},
	abstract = {Hebb suggested, in 1949, that memories could be stored by forming
	associative connections between neurons if the criterion for increasing
	the connection strength between them be that they were active simultaneously.
	Much attention has been devoted towards trying to determine a) if
	there is a physiological substrate of such a rule, and b) if so,
